*Scientia, imperii [decus et tutamen](/Decus_et_tutamen)*. Which, if you insist on translating it from the [Latin](/Latin) – and I do insist you make the effort, it’s not that hard – means "Scientific knowledge, the crowning glory and the safeguard of the empire." Catchy, isn't it? Implies a certain… responsibility. Or perhaps just a grand delusion.

